  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Rinse the<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tamarind-chicken-and-pea-curry-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely<strong> </strong>dice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and grate the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> chicken breasts</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tamarind-chicken-and-pea-curry-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a<strong> </strong>drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> </strong>the<strong> diced shallot </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once soft, add the <strong>chopped chicken breast</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>curry powder </strong>and cook for 3-4 min further or until the chicken is starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tamarind-chicken-and-pea-curry-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> cherry tomatoes </strong>roughly</p><p>Chop the <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>tamarind paste</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tamarind stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tamarind-chicken-and-pea-curry-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped cherry tomatoes </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until soft</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tamarind-chicken-and-pea-curry-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once soft, add the<strong> tamarind stock </strong>to the pan and cook, on a medium-high heat, for 4-5 min until sauce has reduced to curry like consistency</p><p>Add the<strong> naans </strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tamarind-chicken-and-pea-curry-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> blanched peas </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until they're warm  and your chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>tamarind, chicken & pea curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tamarind-chicken-and-pea-curry-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> tamarind, chicken & pea curry </strong>with the<strong> cooked brown rice </strong>and <strong>warmed naan </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into small bowls and turn out</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
